summary: This is an FBI 302 interview report from September 17, 2021, where a witness (referred to as [REDACTED]) is shown photographs and a photo book to identify individuals and recall events related to Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell. The witness describes trips, photographs from her high school years, and specific interactions, including turning over physical evidence (cowboy boots) to the FBI.

events.title: Trip to New Mexico

keyFacts: A witness was shown photographs and a photo book by the FBI and identified Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell.
The witness described a trip to New Mexico funded by Epstein in July or early August when she was a teenager, involving stays in a villa and activities like teaching English.
The witness recalled a specific outing to a movie theater in New Mexico where she sat next to Epstein and Maxwell sat on his other side.
The witness turned over physical evidence (cowboy boots) to the FBI in 2021, which had been requested by the FBI back in 2006.
The witness mentioned keeping a journal around the time of the trip but did not write in detail about what happened.
